ember. Taking us from the antechambers of policymakers in Paris to the docksides of Haiphong and the streets of Hanoi, Vietnam 1946 provides the most vivid account to date of the series of events that would make Vietnam the most embattled area in the world during the Cold War period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aIndochinese War, 1946-1954xCauses. 0aIndochinese War, 1946-1954. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  a1946.  aamerican military.  abritish military.  achina.  achinese.  acold war period.  acomprehensive account.  aengaging.  afrench military.  afrench.  aglobal politics.  aglobal tragedy.  ahaiphong.  ahanoi.  aindochina.  aintense.  amodern history.  anations at war.  anonfiction.  apage turner.  aparis.  apolicymakers.  apolitics.  aprewar events.  aresearch.  arevolution and war.  asecret intelligence documents.  asoutheast asia.  avietnam history.  avietnam war.  avietnam.  awar drama.  awar in indochina.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025602640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094460240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944602423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944602/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY